    "permit_type": "Land Use ReviewType 2 procedureAD: Adjustment",
    "work_description": "Approval of the following Adjustments to Zoning Code regulations for the proposed development on this site: ¿To increase the maximum building setback from the west (NE Cully Blvd.) lot line from 20 feet to 429 feet (Zoning Code Section 33.120.220.C.1). ¿To increase the maximum percentage of the site area that can be asphalt vehicle area from 15% to 21.1% (Zoning Code Section 33.266.130.C.4.a.2). ¿To waive the requirement for a 5-foot-wide, L3 (high screen) perimeter landscaping buffer on the north side of Parking Lot A (Zoning Code Section 33.266.130.G.2.d.2). ¿To waive the requirement for a 5-foot-wide, L2 (low screen) perimeter landscaping buffer on the north side of Parking Lot B (Zoning Code Section 33.266.130.G.2.d.1). The approval is per the approved site plan, Exhibit C-1, and subject to the following conditions: A.As part of the building permit application submittal, each of the required site plans and any additional drawings must reflect the information and design approved by this land use review as indicated in Exhibit C-1. The sheets on which this information appears must be labeled, \"Proposal and design as approved in Case File # LU 24-098136 AD.¿ B.Fully sight-obscuring fencing at least 3.5 feet tall is required along the full length of both sections of the north lot line adjacent to the two new parking lots, as illustrated in Exhibit C-1. C.New trees are required within and around the two new parking lots in the numbers and approximate locations illustrated in Exhibit C-1.",
